<br>
wavecrasher(9/19, procs a slow)/frosty (12/22, procs a dd+debuff)<br>
wavecrasher/anklesmasher(10/22, procs snare)<br>
anklesmasher/frosty<br>
<br>
They all do roughly the same dps (wavecrasher/anklesmasher is slightly lower.. by about 4 or 5dps)<br>
<br>
They all proc at roughly the same rate when I'm at 255 dex<br>
<br>
So, the question I have next is:<br>
<br>
When the changes to slow went in, did the wavecrasher become less useful? (An answer from somebody who used one before and after the change would be wonderful)<br>
<br>
Next question.. has anybody tested snare against frostbite agro wise? (If not, I'll go test it out sometime in the near future)<br>
<br>
I'm leaning towards ditching the frosty because the proc doesn't land on ice based mobs anyway. (Yeah, I know.. resists still have the same agro as spells that land)<br>
<br>
Any suggestions? <p><p align=center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=206624"><img border=0 src="http://members.cox.net/lessiter/lesiter.jpg" ><br>58.98 WarGnome</a><br>
