<br>
on a happy note about WC  when its not resisted its a slow which is a good thing. especially if you happen to be confined to few luxury items in your kit, it helps in non chanter shaman groups. <br>
<br>
I dont like the dps though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udandolo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dandolo1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/28/02 9:17:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3968.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wavecrasher vs Anklesmasher vs Frosty</span><hr size=1> I'm a lvl 60 warrior on Torv and have used WC in prim and FB in off for a few lvls now.<br>
<br>
The patch has had no effect on aggro with this combination, and none specificly with the Wavecrasher.  If you don't have a shammy for HoS/FoS + Dex, or a chanter for Haste + Boon, then in all honestly the proc is too unreliable to be effective.  But I look at it this way - if my group doesn't have a haster/slower, I probably don't want to be in that group.<br>
<br>
With this combo I've had absolutly no problems holding aggro in &quot;my personal hell group&quot;.  lvl 60 epic monk dual weilding, lvl 60 epic rogue, lvl 60 dual epic ranger (who doesn't believe in jolt) and a lvl 59 bard, (plus a chanter and cleric, all in UP).<br>
<br>
But more importantly, when we hit defensive and are doing next to nothing for dmg, these procs will still Always keep the mob intrested.<br>
<br>
Hope that help.  I was offered 45k cash in game for it two weeks ago (CoF is 70k, Fungi is 75k on torv) and declined instantly.  Probably the single best equipment pick up I've ever made.<br>
<br>
